message: "If you use this software, please cite the software record below."
type: software
title: "LLMR: A unified interface for research with Large Language Models in R"
version: "0.6.3"
date-released: 2025-10-11
url: "https://github.com/asanaei/LLMR"
repository-code: "https://github.com/asanaei/LLMR"
authors:
  - family-names: "Sanaei"
    given-names: "Ali"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8513-8169"
    email: "sanaei@uchicago.edu"
    affiliation: "Computational Social Science, University of Chicago"
abstract: >-
  LLMR provides a unified, tidyverse-compatible interface for conducting
  experiments with multiple Large Language Model APIs within R. The package
  supports OpenAI, Anthropic, Groq, Together AI, DeepSeek, Gemini, xAI, Voyage AI,
  and Ollama. It includes parallel execution, caching, error handling, and
  structured-output utilities with local validation.
keywords:
  - "large language models"
  - "R"
  - "API"
  - "experimental design"
  - "computational social science"
  - "natural language processing"
  - "reproducible research"
